                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d936">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13578.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guadalupe</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-23T09:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1914, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Villa this morning said that as long as Carranza believed he could
                    control a packed convention he was willing to submit his <pb facs="0728" n="612"
                        xml:id="pg_612"/> resignation and consider the convention sovereign, but
                    that as soon as a really representative convention composed of all factions was
                    convened in neutral territory, his ambition came to light and he now will stop
                    at nothing. Villa stated that he is waiting here patiently for Convention to
                    act; that he is using no pressure whatever; and that when he is ordered to move
                    south against Carranza he will do so with keen pleasure.</p>
                <p>If consistent before acting upon Canova’s October 22, 7 p.m., please let me know
                    Department’s wishes regarding Vera Cruz.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
